issue.title: Hot reloading - state of the project
issue.body:
Hello, I tried to search "hot reload" via search on website, in GitHub organisation, issues etc.
What I found is a few questions about that as well.

- https://github.com/vapor/vapor/issues/389
- https://github.com/vapor/vapor/issues/311
- https://github.com/vapor/vapor/issues/212
- https://github.com/vapor/vapor/issues/181

So what is the state? Does it working, or should, is it present? From what I tried I didn't noticed.

Can you please consider to create a new page, at least under Leaf tab and describe the current situation of Hot reload feature It's fine to say that's not supported at the moment and contribution is welcome, or provide a few links to workarounds, unofficial solutions.

I beliave that this is a quite common thing that every new developer looking for and there is no answer.

pull_request.body:
- Replace all the lambda deploy workflows with a much less contrived reusable workflow 
- Deletes the now unnecessary (and inefficient) packaging scripts
- Modernize the unit tests workflow
- Replace the projectboard workflow with the one used by other Vapor repos
- Use checkout@v3 in the cloudformation lint workflow

pull_request.title: Use GH OpenAPI spec + swift-oapi-generator to generate GHHooks models
pull_request.body:
Uses Github OpenAPI spec + swift-openapi-generator for generating models for the GHHooks lambda.

The downside is the build time regression as the generator, at least as a plugin, seems not to be fast at all.
The upside is we won't need to make these models / api-endpoints in the future.
